Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1

Thanks for this patch! I think it heads in very much the right direction.
For what its worth, I believe it would be better in the long term to make the modification tracking functionality a wrapper for other interfaces, rather than making it a base class. It is much easier to reuse functionality when its dependencies and structure are explicit, as opposed to the implicit relationships between a class and its abstract bases. (Disclaimer, for reasons I don't understand, other people get less mileage out of this concept of flat hierarchies and aggregation over inheritance than I do, so this advice might not really fit for you.)

Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1

According to your mail, +1 to this approach instead of db based one, glad to see it passed the test. Will review closer asap, let's try to get this worth fix merged on Juno, I still a little worried on the timing and regression risk.

Thanks for working on this and mail the summary to us.

Patch Set 6: Code-Review-2

Based on some discussion on IRC with other glance developers, I think we should fix this in early-ish K. The timing of this fix is a bit worrisome coupled with lack of reviews/clarity of agreement in approach. 

The K development is about to be opened up so, in cases of absolute need for this fix we can think about backport.

Patch Set 6: Workflow-1

IMO we'd -1 on workflow instead of -2 on review for this timing case.

Patch Set 6: -Code-Review

Kilo development can begin.

Patch Set 6:

@Zhi: are you okay with getting into juno rc2? We've a few hours to decide.

Patch Set 6: -Workflow

I don't want to be a blocker, but I personally think landing this in K early with some enhancements and more reviews are better for us, currently I didn't notice any other report on this kind of issue (even I'm sure this is a worth fix for us technically), so the priority of lowing the risk for a stable release is higher then the priority of low probability issue.
